   "source": [
    "# Multiple basins\n",
    "This example demonstrates the power of the `rapbro` interface to Google Earth Engine (GEE) to collect many subbasin attributes associated with multiple coordinate pairs. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "93516826-74e4-4cdb-95a5-39706bb8b89a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from tqdm import tqdm\n",
    "import geopandas as gpd\n",
    "import contextily as cx # You may need to 'conda install contextily' or 'pip install contextily'\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "import rabpro\n",
    "from rabpro.basin_stats import Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "# os.environ['RABPRO_DATA'] = r'X:\\Data' # Point this to your rabpro datapath if it different than the default"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0f842db0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "If you have not authenticated Google Earth Engine yet, this is a good time to do it. Running the following code should prompt you for an authorization token and instructions for getting it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6f31da86-ef71-47f2-9237-338b2990b453",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "```python\n",
    "import ee\n",
    "ee.Authenticate()\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "197eb567-f163-494c-9479-d140814ce8fa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First let's create a list of coordinate pairs that we'll use to delineate our basins of interest. For this example, we'll retrieve the subbasins associated with dams in Sri Lanka. Data are from [VotE-Dams](https://data.ess-dive.lbl.gov/view/doi:10.15485/1843541)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "e045c28a-ea53-4115-831b-110cc92f8ea8",
   "metadata": {},

    "dam_ids = [13331, 13332, 13333, 13334, 13335, 13336, 13337, 13338, 13339, 13340, 13341, 13342, 13343, 13344, 13345, 13346, 13347, 13348, 13349, 13350, 13351, 13352, 13353, 13354, 13355, 13356, 13357, 13358, 13359, 13360, 13361, 13362, 13363, 13364, 13365, 13366, 13367, 13368, 13369, 13370, 13371, 13372, 13373, 13374, 13375, 13376, 13377, 13378, 13379, 13380, 13381, 13382, 13383, 13384, 13385, 13386, 13387, 13388, 13389, 13390, 13391, 13392, 13393, 13394, 13395, 13396, 13397, 22927]\n",
    "dam_das = [116.0, 1.6, 131.0, 4.0, 138.0, 176.0, 0.95, 155.0, 4.15, 2.75, 7.03, 26.0, 32.0, 4.9, 1.08, 58.0, 45.0, 0.79, 992.0, 555.0, 16.16, 834.0, 96.9, 88.0, 5.5, 572.0, 318.0, 5.7, 152.0, 326.0, 405.0, 2.79, 231.0, 213.0, 73.7, 69.2, 598.0, 72.6, 29.7, 30.9, 181.0, 173.6, 834.5, 552.0, 19.2, 26.3, 85.7, 297.25, 102.2, 1350.0, 170.7, 1616.0, 2350.0, 3109.0, 38.7, 26.8, 981.0, 340.0, 311.0, 1160.0, 239.0, 312.0, 183.0, 250.0, 1900.0, 72.0, 549.8, 470.5]\n",
    "vdams_srilanka = pd.DataFrame(data={'coords':dam_coords, 'vote_id':dam_ids, 'da_km2':dam_das})\n",
    "vdams_srilanka.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bec0b73f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We loop through each coordinate pair and delineate its watershed using MERIT (this is only possible if an estimated drainage area is known, which is the case here, else `rabpro` would use HydroBasins), then combine all watershed polygons into a GeoDataFrame. If you want to use MERIT, download tile 'n00e060' following the MERIT download [example](https://github.com/VeinsOfTheEarth/rabpro/blob/main/docs/source/examples/notebooks/downloading_data.ipynb)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "d56356e8-a0ed-4974-8ad8-44ba5359a5e2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if os.path.isfile(\"basins_sl.gpkg\") is False:\n",
    "    basins_sl = []\n",
    "    for i, row in tqdm(vdams_srilanka.iterrows(), total=vdams_srilanka.shape[0]):        \n",
    "        rpo = rabpro.profiler(row['coords'], da=row['da_km2'], verbose=False)\n",
    "        rpo.delineate_basin(force_merit=True)\n",
    "        rpo.watershed['vote_id'] = row['vote_id']\n",
    "        basins_sl.append(rpo.watershed)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    basins_sl = pd.concat(basins_sl)\n",
    "    basins_sl.to_file(\"basins_sl.gpkg\", driver=\"GPKG\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    basins_sl = gpd.read_file(\"basins_sl.gpkg\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ee472c6a-77a1-405b-8357-6f363b386176",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We need to upload our basin vector layer as a GEE asset because it too large to send as a json payload. This can be done manually through the GEE code editor or via `rabpro` automation. This automation requires that you have a writeable Google Cloud Platform (GCP) bucket and that you are authenticated via the command-line to call the `gsutil` and `earthengine` programs. These programs enable sending files to GCP and onward to GEE respectively.\n",
    "\n",
    "For now, you can skip this step as we've uploaded the sl_basins file as a public asset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b4539f74-da5a-4405-a799-03d6acac6215",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "```python\n",
    "gcp_bucket = \"your_gcp_bucket\"\n",
    "gee_user = \"your_gee_username\"\n",
    "zip_path = rabpro.utils.build_gee_vector_asset(basins_sl, \"basins_sl.zip\")\n",
    "your_gee_asset = rabpro.utils.upload_gee_vector_asset(\n",
    "    zip_path, gee_user, gcp_bucket, gcp_folder=\"rabpro\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7a07ce6b-4645-49b1-b2ff-39af540367fd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We'd like to get zonal statistics over each of our delineated basins. We need to first define a list of Google Earth Engine (GEE) datasets we'd like to sample. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "5aaff7f7-131a-4f72-9a71-981d651fa072",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dataset_list = [\n",
    "    Dataset(\n",
    "        \"JRC/GSW1_3/GlobalSurfaceWater\",\n",
    "        \"occurrence\",\n",
    "        time_stats=[\"median\"],\n",
    "        stats=[\"mean\"],\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    Dataset(\n",
    "        \"ECMWF/ERA5_LAND/MONTHLY\",\n",
    "        \"temperature_2m\",\n",
    "        time_stats=[\"median\"],\n",
    "        stats=[\"mean\"],\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    Dataset(\n",
    "        \"UCSB-CHG/CHIRPS/DAILY\", \"precipitation\", time_stats=[\"median\"], stats=[\"mean\"]\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ab60a65b-dc0d-493f-8b7f-8a2070a46fc8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now let's do the sampling with `rabpro.basin_stats.compute()`, format the results, and join it to our basins GeoDataFrame."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "7600a0c1-0344-4a45-9fbe-dede27ae2d60",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "your_gee_asset = 'users/jstacompute/basins_sl'"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "3fa177f6-9037-42e0-946d-44a6c9286d3e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "CPU times: total: 125 ms\n",
      "Wall time: 134 ms\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "%%time\n",
    "# This could take a few minutes to run, depending on how quickly GEE completes your tasks.\n",
    "if not os.path.exists(\"res.gpkg\"):\n",
    "    urls, tasks = rabpro.basin_stats.compute(\n",
    "        dataset_list, gee_feature_path=your_gee_asset, folder=\"rabpro\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    tag_list = [\"wateroccur\", \"temperature_2m\", \"precip\"]\n",
    "    data = rabpro.basin_stats.fetch_gee(urls, tag_list)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    res = gpd.GeoDataFrame(data.merge(basins_sl, on='vote_id'))\n",
    "    res = res.set_geometry(\"geometry\")\n",
    "    res.to_file(\"res.gpkg\", driver=\"GPKG\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    res = gpd.read_file(\"res.gpkg\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2b466ebc-6c42-40b4-8b1a-5ba6e0c0d134",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, we can visualize our results!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "b40c3e25-9029-4461-9191-c0007df0c50e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x720 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def build_panel(col_name, col_label, axis):\n",
    "    axis.set_xlim([left-0.5, right+0.5])\n",
    "    axis.set_ylim([bot-0.2, top+0.2])\n",
    "    axis.set_axis_off()\n",
    "    res.plot(\n",
    "        ax=axis,\n",
    "        column=col_name,\n",
    "        legend=True,\n",
    "        legend_kwds={\"label\": col_label, \"orientation\": \"horizontal\", \"pad\": 0.01},\n",
    "    )    \n",
    "    cx.add_basemap(axis, zoom=10, crs=res.crs, attribution=\"\")\n",
    "    return axis\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "left, bot, right, top = res.total_bounds\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(10, 10))\n",
    "ax = [\n",
    "    build_panel(col_name, col_label, ax[i])\n",
    "    for col_name, col_label, i in zip(\n",
    "        [x for x in res.columns[1:4]],\n",
    "        [\"Water occurence %\", \"Temperature (K)\", \"Precipitation (mm/day)\"],\n",
    "        range(0, 3),\n",
    "    )\n",
    "]"
   ]
  }
 ],
